# __PACKAGE_NAME__

__DESCRIPTION__

Scaffolded by the `create-pure-module` skill, following the op-sqlite
architecture: the only codegen'd TurboModule method is a blocking-synchronous
`install()` that hands the JSI `Runtime` and `CallInvoker` to hand-written C++
(`cpp/__PREFIX__Module.cpp`). Everything else is a plain JSI `HostObject` —
see `cpp/ExampleHostObject.{hpp,cpp}` for the sync/async method pattern to
copy for real functionality.

## Layout

- `cpp/` — the C++ core: `__PREFIX__Module.{hpp,cpp}` (install/invalidate
  entry point), `ExampleHostObject.{hpp,cpp}` (template HostObject),
  `__PREFIX__ThreadPool.{hpp,cpp}` (per-HostObject background work),
  `types.hpp` (the `JSVariant` type every JSI value should round-trip
  through), `utils.{hpp,cpp}` (`to_jsi()`/`to_variant()` — use these for
  every JSI <-> C++ conversion; `create_object_array()` — builds an array of
  same-shaped objects while caching each column's `jsi::PropNameID` once
  instead of once per cell; `promisify()` — the async Promise helper),
  `macros.hpp` (the `__PREFIX_UPPER___HFN*` HostFunction shorthand),
  `logs.h` (platform log macros).
- `ios/` — the Objective-C++ TurboModule (`__PREFIX__.{h,mm}`) that exposes
  `install()` and forwards into `cpp/`.
- `android/` — CMake + prefab build, the fbjni JNI bridge
  (`cpp-adapter.cpp`), and the Kotlin TurboModule (`__PREFIX__Bridge.kt`,
  `__PREFIX__Module.kt`, `__PREFIX__Package.kt`).
- `src/` — `Native__PREFIX__.ts` (the minimal codegen spec) and `index.ts`
  (calls `install()` once, reads `global.__GLOBAL_PROXY__`, exports a typed
  wrapper).

## Adding functionality

New functionality gets its own `HostObject` under `cpp/` (copy
`ExampleHostObject` as a starting point), registered on the proxy inside
`install()` in `cpp/__PREFIX__Module.cpp`. No codegen or TurboModule spec
changes are needed for new methods — that's the point of this architecture.
Expose a typed wrapper for it from `src/index.ts`.

Convert every JSI value through `to_jsi()`/`to_variant()` in `cpp/utils.cpp`
rather than reading/writing `jsi::Value` by hand — add a new `JSVariant`
alternative in `cpp/types.hpp` if you need to pass a shape the existing ones
don't cover. When a HostFunction returns an array of same-shaped objects
(e.g. rows), use `create_object_array()` instead of building each object's
`jsi::PropNameID`s inline — it creates them once and reuses them across
every row, which matters once you're past a handful of rows.

## Local development

This package has no bundled example app. To try it out:

1. `yarn install` (or `npm install`) in this directory.
2. Create a test app (e.g. `npx @react-native-community/cli init`) and add
   this package as a local dependency (`npm link`, `yalc`, or a `file:`
   dependency in the test app's package.json).
3. iOS: `cd ios && pod install` in the test app.
4. Android: just build normally — prefab headers are wired up in
   `android/build.gradle`.
